Description: Data validation using Python type hints (Avalan PPA pin)
 Pydantic is a data validation library that uses Python type hints
 to perform runtime parsing and validation. The Avalan PPA ships
 pydantic 2.6.4 because Noble carries pydantic 1.x (below Avalan's
 floor) and Debian sid's pydantic 2.13.x Build-Depends on a
 pydantic-core version Noble's archive cannot supply. 2.6.4 pairs
 lock-step with pydantic-core 2.16.3 (also in this PPA).
